@startuml Sequence_Diagram_Admin_Monitoring
!theme plain
title Admin Monitoring Dashboard - Sequence Diagram

actor Admin as admin
participant "C&C Dashboard\nUI" as dashboard
participant "API Client" as apiclient
participant "Flask API\nMonitoring BP" as api
participant "Monitoring Service" as monitor
participant "System Monitor" as sysmon
participant "Container Monitor" as containermon
participant "Component Monitor" as compmon

autonumber

admin -> dashboard: Open C&C Dashboard

dashboard -> apiclient: GET /api/monitoring/status
apiclient -> api: HTTP GET + JWT (admin token)

api -> api: Verify JWT + Check role=admin

api -> monitor: get_overall_status()

monitor -> sysmon: get_system_metrics()
note right of sysmon
  Using psutil library:
  - CPU: 25.3%
  - Memory: 45.2%
  - Disk: 60.1%
  - Uptime: 86400s
  - Processes: 120
end note
sysmon -> monitor: {cpu, memory, disk, uptime}

monitor -> containermon: get_container_status()
note right of containermon
  Check backend & database containers:
  - Backend: running, CPU 15%, Mem 512MB
  - Database: running, CPU 8%, Mem 1024MB
end note
containermon -> monitor: {containers: [...]}

monitor -> compmon: get_component_status()
note right of compmon
  Health check each API component:
  - api-auth: 125ms response
  - api-quiz: 145ms response
  - api-courses: 120ms response
  - api-chatbot: 2500ms (calling OpenAI)
  - database-connection: 50ms
  - file-storage: 85ms
end note
compmon -> monitor: {components: [...]}

monitor -> monitor: Aggregate status\n(priority-based)
note right of monitor
  Logic:
  - If any critical: status = "critical" 🔴
  - If any degraded: status = "degraded" 🟠
  - If any warning: status = "warning" 🟡
  - Else: status = "healthy" 🟢
  
  In this case: all healthy → 🟢
end note

monitor -> monitor: Check alerts\n(threshold-based)
note right of monitor
  Thresholds:
  - CPU > 90%: critical ❌
  - Memory > 90%: critical ❌
  - Disk > 90%: critical ❌
  - Response > 5000ms: warning ⚠️
  - Error rate > 10%: warning ⚠️
  
  Current: No alerts ✓
end note

monitor -> api: {status, system, containers, components, alerts}

api -> apiclient: HTTP 200 + JSON

apiclient -> dashboard: Response received

dashboard -> dashboard: Render dashboard
note right of dashboard
  - Main indicator: 🟢 HEALTHY
  - System metrics with progress bars
  - Container list with status
  - Component list with response times
  - Alerts section (empty/green)
  - Last updated: <timestamp>
end note

dashboard -> admin: Display C&C Dashboard

note over admin
  Admin sees:
  ┌─────────────────────┐
  │ 🟢 E-LEARNING C&C    │
  │ Status: HEALTHY     │
  ├─────────────────────┤
  │ SYSTEM STATUS       │
  │ CPU: 25.3% ░░░░░░░ │
  │ RAM: 45.2% ░░░░░░░ │
  │ Disk: 60.1% ░░░░░░│
  ├─────────────────────┤
  │ CONTAINERS          │
  │ 🟢 backend (running)│
  │ 🟢 database (running)
  ├─────────────────────┤
  │ COMPONENTS          │
  │ 🟢 api-auth: 125ms  │
  │ 🟢 api-quiz: 145ms  │
  │ 🟢 api-courses: 120ms
  ├─────────────────────┤
  │ ALERTS              │
  │ ✓ No active alerts  │
  └─────────────────────┘
end note

note over dashboard
  Dashboard auto-refreshes
  every 5 seconds
end note

loop Every 5 seconds
  dashboard -> apiclient: GET /api/monitoring/status
  apiclient -> api: HTTP GET
  api -> monitor: get_overall_status()
  monitor -> dashboard: Updated metrics
  dashboard -> dashboard: Refresh UI
end loop

note right of admin
  Admin can:
  - Monitor real-time metrics
  - Detect issues early
  - View historical trends (future)
  - Get alerts via email (future)
  - Trigger auto-scaling (future)
end note

@enduml
